<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - High-pressure Oil Pump -
        Installation - High-pressure Oil Pump and Drive Gear
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="6">
        <title>High-pressure Oil Pump and Drive Gear</title>
        <figure id="f1201111" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3513A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing High-pressure Oil Pump and Gasket</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure Oil Pump</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the high-pressure oil pump drive gear into the opening on top of the front cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the high-pressure oil pump with the gasket against the front cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201112" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3514A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing High-pressure Oil Pump Mounting Bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure Oil Pump</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install and tighten the two mounting bolts to the special torque value.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201113" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3263.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Drive Gear Bolt</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drive Gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drive Gear Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Washer</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the drive gear bolt and washer to secure the drive gear to the high-pressure oil
                pump. Tighten bolt to the special torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201115" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3516.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Applying RTV Sealant to the Drive Gear Access Cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drive Gear</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure Oil Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">RTV Bead</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Cover</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply RTV sealant to the drive gear access cover mounting surface.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2051102" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg9/EG9139.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Install Drive Gear Access Cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Drive Gear Access Cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting Bolt (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the access cover and two mounting bolts. Tighten the bolts to the standard torque
                value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the engine wiring harness connector to the IPR valve solenoid.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201121" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg9/EG9136.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing High-pressure Oil Supply Hoses</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure Oil Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">High-pressure Oil Supply Hoses</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hose Clamp</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the protective caps from the fittings. Install both high-pressure oil supply hoses at
                the high-pressure oil pump and cylinder head. Make sure the hose fittings snap into place.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
